title: Grateful Dead Live at Dean Smith Center on 1993-03-24
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw
Stagger Lee
Wang Dang Doodle
It Must Have Been The Roses
Stuck Inside Of Mobile, With The Memphis Blues Again
Tennessee Jed
Let It Grow

Set 2

Here Comes Sunshine
Playing In The Band
Box Of Rain
Crazy Fingers
Drums
Space
Spanish Jam
Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad
Throwing Stones
Not Fade Away

Encore:
Lucy In The Sky With Diamonds

Dan Healy gave a lecture at UNC that day (which was well recieved) and gave out SBD patches for the show that night.

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Vince Welnick - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text:
End of an era? "Dan Healy gave a lecture at UNC that day (which was well recieved) and gave out SBD patches for the show that night."

Rumor has it that the digital patches out at these shows provided by Dan marked the end of his career w GD.  Administration was highly pissed.
That said, these were the LOUDEST and CLEAREST shows ever.  The sound was colossal.   Music adequate, but fading fast.

Thank you, Dans Dan Healy did indeed give out soundboard patches at these shows. He literally tossed 2 XLR Cables to us tapers and said "here, you figure it out.". It may have been Dan Liff's deck that we used as the lead deck out of the soundboard because of it's connectivity. Thanks to both Dan's! If Dan Liff has passed away (it says "rip" next to his name), I hope he is in a better place. He was a nice guy.
